Female imago. Length (mm): body, 12.1–15.0; fore wing, 15.5–17.0; hind wing, 6.0–7.2. Similar to male, except pigmentation more marked. Sternum VIII with fused anteromedian sockets (
<figureCitation box="[1107,1332,766,791]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStart-1="FIGURES 13 – 24" captionStart-2="FIGURES 25 – 34" captionStartId-0="4.[151,264,1834,1857]" captionStartId-1="5.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionStartId-2="7.[151,264,1939,1962]" captionTargetBox-0="[229,1357,377,1813]" captionTargetBox-1="[235,1359,202,1827]" captionTargetBox-2="[212,1363,202,1896]" captionTargetId-0="figure@4.[229,1357,373,1813]" captionTargetId-1="figure@5.[211,1367,193,1852]" captionTargetId-2="figure@7.[212,1363,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId-0="4" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionTargetPageId-2="7" captionText-0="FIGURES 1 – 12. Campsurus latipennis, adult. Male imago: 1, genitalia, ventral view (v. v.); 2, details of pedestal, v. v.; 3, detail of penes and pedestals, v. v.; 4 – 5, penes, lateral view (l. v.); 6, genitalia, l. v. SEM photographs: 9, genitalia, v. v.; 10, detail of microtrichia on sternum IX; 11, pedestal, v. v.; 12, detail of penes, v. v. Female adult: 7, abdominal sternum VIII; 8, detail of sockets. Abbreviations: bp = base of penes, ml = main lobe of penes, mp = median projection of sternum IX, ps = parastylus, sl = secondary lobe of penes." captionText-1="FIGURES 13 – 24. Campsurus latipennis, nymph. 13, head, d. v. (long setae omitted); 14, left mandible, d. v. (row of filtering setae indicated with dashed line); 15, right mandible, v. v. (filtering setae as in previous figure); 16, apex of right mandibular tusk; 17, foreleg, d. v. (filtering setae not shown); 18, foreleg, v. v. (only filtering setae are indicated, with dashed lines); 19, foretarsal claw; 20, middle leg, d. v.; 21, middle tarsal claw; 22, hind leg, d. v.; 23, hind tarsal claw; 24, paraprocts with spines indicated (arrow)." captionText-2="FIGURES 25 – 34. Campsurus salobra sp. nov., adult: 25, male genitalia, v. v.; 26, same, l. v.; 27, female sternum VIII; 28, detail of female sockets. SEM photographs: 29, male genitalia, v. v. (with detail of microtrichiae); 30, apical portion of penes, v. v.; 31, female sterna VIII – X; 32, female sockets (with detail of microtrichia); 33, egg, convex side; 34, detail of capped pole." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/838440/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/838442/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/838444/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">
Figs. 
<date box="[1172,1285,767,791]" pageId="8" pageNumber="309" value="1931-02-07" valueMax="1931-02-28" valueMin="1931-02-07">2 7–28, 31</date>
–32
</figureCitation>
), sockets relatively long and opening towards median line (
<figureCitation box="[707,845,802,827]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 34" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1939,1962]" captionTargetBox="[212,1363,202,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[212,1363,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 34. Campsurus salobra sp. nov., adult: 25, male genitalia, v. v.; 26, same, l. v.; 27, female sternum VIII; 28, detail of female sockets. SEM photographs: 29, male genitalia, v. v. (with detail of microtrichiae); 30, apical portion of penes, v. v.; 31, female sterna VIII – X; 32, female sockets (with detail of microtrichia); 33, egg, convex side; 34, detail of capped pole." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838444/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">Figs. 31–32</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1439]" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">
Egg. Length, 314 µm; maximum width, 263 µm. Ovoid outline, bowl-shaped, one polar cap present, relatively large (length 32 µm, width 142µm), formed by 
<emphasis box="[687,721,876,899]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">ca.</emphasis>
10 long coiled threads (
<figureCitation box="[994,1132,874,899]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 34" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1939,1962]" captionTargetBox="[212,1363,202,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[212,1363,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 34. Campsurus salobra sp. nov., adult: 25, male genitalia, v. v.; 26, same, l. v.; 27, female sternum VIII; 28, detail of female sockets. SEM photographs: 29, male genitalia, v. v. (with detail of microtrichiae); 30, apical portion of penes, v. v.; 31, female sterna VIII – X; 32, female sockets (with detail of microtrichia); 33, egg, convex side; 34, detail of capped pole." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838444/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">Figs. 33–34</figureCitation>
). Polar cap 0.5× maximum width of egg.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
