<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="309" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1439]" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1018,1043]" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Molineri &amp; Salles, 2017" authorityName="Molineri &amp; Salles" authorityYear="2017" box="[333,558,1018,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salobra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[333,558,1018,1043]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">Campsurus salobra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[571,666,1018,1043]" pageId="8" pageNumber="309" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[571,666,1018,1043]" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from all other species of the genus by the following combination of characters. In the adult: 1) posterior margin of male abdominal sternum IX convex and subtriangular, medially rounded (mp in 
<figureCitation box="[614,756,1090,1115]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 34" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1939,1962]" captionTargetBox="[212,1363,202,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[212,1363,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 34. Campsurus salobra sp. nov., adult: 25, male genitalia, v. v.; 26, same, l. v.; 27, female sternum VIII; 28, detail of female sockets. SEM photographs: 29, male genitalia, v. v. (with detail of microtrichiae); 30, apical portion of penes, v. v.; 31, female sterna VIII – X; 32, female sockets (with detail of microtrichia); 33, egg, convex side; 34, detail of capped pole." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838444/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">Figs. 25, 29</figureCitation>
), surface covered with microtrichiae (
<figureCitation box="[1199,1287,1090,1115]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 34" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1939,1962]" captionTargetBox="[212,1363,202,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[212,1363,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 34. Campsurus salobra sp. nov., adult: 25, male genitalia, v. v.; 26, same, l. v.; 27, female sternum VIII; 28, detail of female sockets. SEM photographs: 29, male genitalia, v. v. (with detail of microtrichiae); 30, apical portion of penes, v. v.; 31, female sterna VIII – X; 32, female sockets (with detail of microtrichia); 33, egg, convex side; 34, detail of capped pole." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838444/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); 2) pedestal bases well separated from each other, pedestals subquadrate with outer-posterior margin projected forming a short and acute parastylus (p in 
<figureCitation box="[455,596,1162,1187]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 34" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1939,1962]" captionTargetBox="[212,1363,202,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[212,1363,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 34. Campsurus salobra sp. nov., adult: 25, male genitalia, v. v.; 26, same, l. v.; 27, female sternum VIII; 28, detail of female sockets. SEM photographs: 29, male genitalia, v. v. (with detail of microtrichiae); 30, apical portion of penes, v. v.; 31, female sterna VIII – X; 32, female sockets (with detail of microtrichia); 33, egg, convex side; 34, detail of capped pole." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838444/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">Figs. 25, 29</figureCitation>
); 3) penes separated and slightly diverging distally (
<figureCitation box="[1198,1424,1162,1187]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 34" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1939,1962]" captionTargetBox="[212,1363,202,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[212,1363,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 34. Campsurus salobra sp. nov., adult: 25, male genitalia, v. v.; 26, same, l. v.; 27, female sternum VIII; 28, detail of female sockets. SEM photographs: 29, male genitalia, v. v. (with detail of microtrichiae); 30, apical portion of penes, v. v.; 31, female sterna VIII – X; 32, female sockets (with detail of microtrichia); 33, egg, convex side; 34, detail of capped pole." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838444/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">Figs. 25–26, 29–30</figureCitation>
), each arm formed by a large and sclerotized lobe (ml in 
<figureCitation box="[771,853,1198,1223]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 34" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1939,1962]" captionTargetBox="[212,1363,202,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[212,1363,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 34. Campsurus salobra sp. nov., adult: 25, male genitalia, v. v.; 26, same, l. v.; 27, female sternum VIII; 28, detail of female sockets. SEM photographs: 29, male genitalia, v. v. (with detail of microtrichiae); 30, apical portion of penes, v. v.; 31, female sterna VIII – X; 32, female sockets (with detail of microtrichia); 33, egg, convex side; 34, detail of capped pole." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838444/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
), and a relatively large secondary membranous lobe (sl in 
<figureCitation box="[219,304,1234,1259]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 34" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1939,1962]" captionTargetBox="[212,1363,202,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[212,1363,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 34. Campsurus salobra sp. nov., adult: 25, male genitalia, v. v.; 26, same, l. v.; 27, female sternum VIII; 28, detail of female sockets. SEM photographs: 29, male genitalia, v. v. (with detail of microtrichiae); 30, apical portion of penes, v. v.; 31, female sterna VIII – X; 32, female sockets (with detail of microtrichia); 33, egg, convex side; 34, detail of capped pole." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838444/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
); 4) medium to large size (length of male fore wings 10.6–12.0 mm); 5) female sternum VIII with anteromedian paired sockets (arrow in 
<figureCitation box="[595,732,1270,1295]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 34" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1939,1962]" captionTargetBox="[212,1363,202,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[212,1363,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 34. Campsurus salobra sp. nov., adult: 25, male genitalia, v. v.; 26, same, l. v.; 27, female sternum VIII; 28, detail of female sockets. SEM photographs: 29, male genitalia, v. v. (with detail of microtrichiae); 30, apical portion of penes, v. v.; 31, female sterna VIII – X; 32, female sockets (with detail of microtrichia); 33, egg, convex side; 34, detail of capped pole." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838444/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">Figs. 27, 31</figureCitation>
), sockets relatively long and rounded, opening toward medial line (arrow in 
<figureCitation box="[309,393,1306,1331]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 34" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1939,1962]" captionTargetBox="[212,1363,202,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[212,1363,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 34. Campsurus salobra sp. nov., adult: 25, male genitalia, v. v.; 26, same, l. v.; 27, female sternum VIII; 28, detail of female sockets. SEM photographs: 29, male genitalia, v. v. (with detail of microtrichiae); 30, apical portion of penes, v. v.; 31, female sterna VIII – X; 32, female sockets (with detail of microtrichia); 33, egg, convex side; 34, detail of capped pole." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838444/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
); 6) medium sized polar cap present in the egg (
<figureCitation box="[928,1065,1306,1331]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 34" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1939,1962]" captionTargetBox="[212,1363,202,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[212,1363,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 34. Campsurus salobra sp. nov., adult: 25, male genitalia, v. v.; 26, same, l. v.; 27, female sternum VIII; 28, detail of female sockets. SEM photographs: 29, male genitalia, v. v. (with detail of microtrichiae); 30, apical portion of penes, v. v.; 31, female sterna VIII – X; 32, female sockets (with detail of microtrichia); 33, egg, convex side; 34, detail of capped pole." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838444/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">Figs. 33–34</figureCitation>
), polar cap 0.5× maximum width of egg.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="309" type="discussion">
